The paper deals with algorithms for laying out large graphs and proposes a method for browsing them. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed method involves creating a sequence of layers and rendering only those entities that intersect the current viewport, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions preprocessing the graph, which suggests that it may involve database systems (cs.DB). The ability to explore a graph on a finer level of detail suggests that the paper may also involve information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for browsing large graphs, which may fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
